Download the Wan2_1_VACE_1_3B_preview_bf16.safetensors file and put it into ComfyUI>models>diffusion_models, then select it in the "WanVideo VACE Model Select"

The rest of the models are the same as base Wan2.1. If you do not already have Wan2.1 Setup, GO TO THIS LINK AND WATCH THE VIDEO:
https://youtu.be/D4VLXF4ZNq0?si=2c3ekxuDbKbc5m-K

I just used florence2 segmentation for this. If you're removing a subject, they're probably well defined in the image. The Points Editor option is also available if you'd like to use that instead. Just connect the  SAM2Segmentation to the grow mask node. 

If there are multiple subjects or subjects moving out of frame, you are better off using the points editor version.

Also DO NOT USE MASK BLURRING. VACE doesn't handle the blurring properly and you'll be left with artifacts
I've found flux1-fill to be ideal for this application. You can also try flux1-dev, but I had a hard time matching the colors without flux1-fill
Refer to the youtube video for instructions for how to run the workflow if you need help:

people, person, man, woman, human, moving, walking, overexposure, static, blurred details, subtitles, paintings, pictures, still, overall gray, worst quality, low quality, JPEG compression residue, cluttered background,
